rockchip-vaapi (1.0.11+ysp2) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Add a checksum-pinned ITU-T H.264 and libvpx VP9 conformance gate, with
    explicit VA-API, software-fallback, and kernel-crash quarantine paths.
  * Reconstruct H.264 High-profile scaling lists from VAIQMatrixBufferH264;
    the HCAFR1_HHI conformance vector is now bit-exact.
  * Withdraw H.264 Constrained Baseline after SVA_Base_B exposed corrupt MPP
    output; applications now fall back to software for that profile.
  * Bound decoded NV12 copies and size export surfaces for MPP's aligned
    strides, fixing the independent Track 14 userspace overflow.
  * Add ASan/UBSan builds, unit coverage, clang-tidy, AArch64 cross-build CI,
    and a guarded manual ROCK 5B hardware job.

 -- Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>  Tue, 21 Jul 2026 18:05:57 -0700

rockchip-vaapi (1.0.11+ysp1) resolute; urgency=medium

  Fork build (yisding/rockchip-vaapi). Correctness fixes, all validated on a
  ROCK 5B (RK3588, vendor MPP on kernel 6.18) with a software-vs-VAAPI
  framemd5 bit-exactness gate (tests/validate.sh, make check).

  * H.264: re-emit PPS before every frame with num_ref_idx_*_default taken
    from the frame's slice parameters, instead of hardcoding 1. Fixes heavy
    corruption on multi-reference / B-frame streams (was 109-117 of 120
    frames wrong at ref=4:bframes=3). ref in {1,2,4,8} x bframes in {0,2,3}
    and a 4K clip are now bit-exact.
  * VP9: retry decode_put_packet while draining output on MPP input
    backpressure, instead of treating a full-queue failure as fatal and
    silently dropping frames (was up to 38 of 120 packets dropped,
    nondeterministically). VP9 now 10/10 bit-exact across repeated runs.
  * VP9: route output frames by the submission FIFO rather than packet PTS,
    since a show_existing_frame repeat of a hidden altref can carry the
    altref packet's PTS and desync all later frames.
  * Advertise only validated profiles (H.264 CB/Main/High, VP9 Profile 0).
    HEVC (no header reconstruction), VP8 (segfault), and 10-bit (NV15/P010
    layout mismatch) are withdrawn so apps fall back to software instead of
    failing. RTFormat no longer claims 10-bit.
  * debconf: default the system-wide MOZ_DISABLE_RDD_SANDBOX prompt to false
    and document that it disables Firefox's media sandbox for all users.
  * Build: DESTDIR/PREFIX/multiarch-aware Makefile, drop sudo from
    make install, add make check gate. Link without -ldl (unused).

 -- Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>  Tue, 21 Jul 2026 12:10:00 +0000

rockchip-vaapi (1.0.11-1) noble; urgency=high

  * Fix 4K@60fps stability: >30000 frames decoded without NS_ERROR in Firefox,
    including clean DASH quality switches. Seven improvements:
  * CMA requirement documented and DTB fix: 4K VP9 decode needs ≥512MB CMA.
    The RK3588 DTB hardcodes CMA with a fixed reg address that overrides any
    cma= kernel command line parameter. Fix: patch the DTB with fdtput to change
    the reg size from 256MB to 512MB, or alternatively add cma=512M to the
    kernel command line (if the DTB node is removed/reusable). Without this,
    4K playback fails after ~75 frames with NS_ERROR_DOM_MEDIA_FATAL_ERR.
  * Conditional logging: LOG was unconditional fprintf to stderr on every VA-API
    call (~500/s at 60fps). This stalled Firefox's decode thread enough to
    trigger NS_ERROR at DASH segment boundaries. LOG is now a no-op unless the
    RK_VAAPI_LOG environment variable is set to a file path.
  * COMPOSED_LAYERS in ExportSurfaceHandle: mpv and GStreamer request
    VA_EXPORT_SURFACE_COMPOSED_LAYERS (flags=0x9). Now returns DRM_FORMAT_NV12
    (or DRM_FORMAT_P010 for 10-bit) with 2 planes in one layer instead of always
    using the R8/GR88 split required by Firefox. Fixes green screen in mpv
    --vo=dmabuf-wayland.
  * rk_GetImage implemented: was a stub returning success without copying
    data. vaapi-copy mode showed a green screen; now copies Y+UV planes from
    priv_buf with proper stride re-packing to the image buffer layout.
  * rk_DeriveImage: returned ERROR_INVALID_SURFACE due to s->frame always being
    NULL (removed in v1.0.10). Now returns ERROR_OPERATION_FAILED explicitly so
    callers fall back to vaGetImage cleanly.
  * Async EndPicture: EndPicture previously blocked for up to 1671ms on large
    4K keyframes (835KB first frame of each DASH segment). Firefox's media
    pipeline froze during this stall and fired NS_ERROR. EndPicture now returns
    immediately after decode_put_packet; SyncSurface handles all waiting.
  * Sync in ExportSurfaceHandle: with async EndPicture, Firefox calls
    ExportSurfaceHandle before SyncSurface. The EGLImage was created from stale
    priv_buf data causing a green bar / progressive color artifacts. If a decode
    is in progress when ExportSurfaceHandle is called, it now syncs the surface
    first to guarantee the exported DMA-BUF contains the correct frame.

 -- Eduardo García-Mádico Portabella <woodyst@gmail.com>  Wed, 28 May 2026 00:00:00 +0200

rockchip-vaapi (1.0.10-1) noble; urgency=high

  * Fix "saltando frames" (wrong video frames in Firefox compositor): MPP uses
    only ~3 internal DMA-BUF buffers for 4K VP9 decode regardless of how many
    VA surfaces Firefox allocates. Previously assign_mpp_frame stored MPP's
    MppFrame reference in the surface and exposed MPP's buffer fd directly;
    BeginPicture called mpp_frame_deinit() which released MPP's reference,
    allowing it to immediately reuse the physical buffer while Firefox's
    compositor thread still held an export_fd pointing to it.
  * Fix: each VA surface now owns a dedicated permanent DMA-BUF (priv_buf,
    allocated at CreateSurfaces). assign_mpp_frame copies decoded pixels from
    MPP's internal buffer into this dedicated buffer, then releases MPP's
    buffer immediately. prime_fd is set once at CreateSurfaces and never
    changes for the surface's lifetime. ExportSurfaceHandle always exports
    the surface's own stable buffer, which Firefox can hold indefinitely
    without risk of MPP overwriting it.
  * Allocation size for dedicated buffer raised from hs*vs*3/2 to hs*vs*3 to
    cover both NV12 (8-bit) and P010 (10-bit YUV420) in a single allocation.
  * SyncSurface: replace priv_buf-presence shortcut with ctx_id==0 check to
    distinguish "placeholder not yet decoded" from "decode in progress".
  * Fix H.264 decode never producing any frame (every SyncSurface timed out →
    NS_ERROR_DOM_MEDIA_FATAL_ERR): h264_write_sps emitted only 7 bits between
    profile_idc and level_idc instead of the required 8 (constraint_set0..5 +
    reserved_zero_2bits). The missing bit misaligned the entire SPS RBSP, so
    MPP could not parse it and never raised the info_change event needed to
    allocate output buffers. Now writes the correct 8 bits; verified the
    reconstructed SPS round-trips to profile/level/dimensions.
  * Fix VP9 altref crash regression: the altref fallback (when MPP does not
    output a hidden frame within the poll window) was still closing the
    surface's prime_fd and setting it to -1, left over from v1.0.9. With the
    new permanent per-surface priv_buf, that destroyed the surface's only DMA-BUF
    fd; when the slot was later reused for a shown frame, assign_mpp_frame copied
    pixels into priv_buf but no longer reassigns prime_fd, leaving it -1 →
    ExportSurfaceHandle returned ERROR_INVALID_SURFACE → NS_ERROR_DOM_MEDIA_FATAL_ERR.
    The fallback now keeps prime_fd valid (placeholder content) so export always
    succeeds.
  * Fix Firefox falling back to software after ~160 frames of 4K VP9
    (NS_ERROR_DOM_MEDIA_FATAL_ERR): the altref (show_frame=0) EndPicture poll
    blocked the decode thread for the full poll window (up to 500ms) on every
    hidden frame, because MPP decodes altrefs internally as references but never
    outputs them via decode_get_frame in this environment. The per-altref stalls
    accumulated until Firefox's decode pipeline underran and declared a fatal
    error. Altref frames are now sent to MPP (still decoded as references) and
    their surface marked decoded immediately with no poll; the permanent priv_buf
    keeps ExportSurfaceHandle valid, and the next frame's pre-drain still recovers
    altref content if MPP emits it late (verified: barcode hidden-frame checks
    still pass). Altref surfaces are also no longer enqueued in the PTS-routing
    FIFO, since MPP never produces a matching output to advance the head past them.
  * assign_mpp_frame: adopt MPP's real hor/ver strides (e.g. 3840x2176 for 4K)
    for both the priv_buf copy and the exported descriptor, so the DMA-BUF layout
    is self-consistent and a non-4K stride mismatch can no longer overflow.
  * Stop advertising AV1 (VAProfileAV1Profile0/1). VA-API delivers AV1 as a
    parsed VAPictureParameterBufferAV1 plus headerless tile data, but MPP needs
    a complete OBU bytestream (sequence header + frame header + tile group OBUs)
    which would have to be reconstructed from the struct. Until that serializer
    exists, advertising AV1 made Firefox attempt it, stall 3s per frame in
    SyncSurface and fall back; not advertising it lets Firefox pick VP9
    (hardware-decoded) directly for AV1-capable content.

 -- Eduardo García-Mádico Portabella <woodyst@gmail.com>  Thu, 28 May 2026 20:00:00 +0000

rockchip-vaapi (1.0.9-1) noble; urgency=high

  * Fix VP9 altref (show_frame=0) ExportSurfaceHandle crash: MPP does output
    altref frames via decode_get_frame (prior assumption that it never did was
    wrong). EndPicture for altref frames now polls MPP for up to 50ms; if MPP
    delivers the frame within that window the surface gets a valid DMA-BUF fd.
    This allows Firefox to call ExportSurfaceHandle on altref surfaces without
    receiving ERROR_INVALID_SURFACE, eliminating the NS_ERROR_DOM_MEDIA_FATAL_ERR
    crash at DASH quality switches where Firefox may reference the altref surface
    via show_existing_frame. If MPP does not output within 50ms (safety fallback)
    the surface is still marked decoded with prime_fd=-1, same as v1.0.8.
  * Fix VP9 altref temporal glitch: since altref surfaces now carry the correct
    decoded content, show_existing_frame references to them display the right
    frame instead of producing a blank/error screen.
  * Add src/gen_test_video.py: generates 640×480 30fps YUV4MPEG2 test video
    with sinusoidal sprites and a binary barcode strip encoding the frame number.
  * Add src/va_barcode_test.c: VA-API hardware decode correctness test that
    decodes IVF/VP9 streams and verifies each exported frame's barcode matches
    the expected source frame number. Tests both shown and hidden (altref) frames.
    Build: gcc -O1 -o va_barcode_test src/va_barcode_test.c -lva -lva-drm -ldrm
           -I/usr/include/libdrm

 -- Eduardo García-Mádico Portabella <woodyst@gmail.com>  Thu, 28 May 2026 16:00:00 +0000

rockchip-vaapi (1.0.8-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Fix H.264 decode: mpp_init must be called before MPP_DEC_SET_CFG and
    MPP_SET_OUTPUT_BLOCK (mpp_init resets all prior configuration); previously
    every H.264 frame timed out in SyncSurface because non-blocking mode was
    never applied.
  * Fix VP9 altref temporal glitch: invalidate prime_fd when a hidden
    (show_frame=0) altref frame is decoded. MPP never outputs altref frames via
    decode_get_frame, so the surface retains the fd from its previous use as a
    P-frame. If Firefox later issues show_existing_frame pointing to that surface,
    ExportSurfaceHandle now returns VA_STATUS_ERROR_INVALID_SURFACE instead of
    serving stale content, eliminating frames-from-the-past appearing mixed with
    current frames.
  * SyncSurface: return VA_STATUS_ERROR_DECODING_ERROR on 3s drain timeout
    instead of SUCCESS, so callers can distinguish a properly decoded surface
    from one that was never assigned an MPP frame.
  * do_h264_decode / do_generic_decode: mark render_target as decoded
    immediately when no VASliceDataBufferType is found (BeginPicture+EndPicture
    without slice data, e.g. after a crash recovery sequence).
  * do_generic_decode: scale EndPicture poll window with packet size
    (min 500ms, max 3000ms) so large 4K VP9 keyframes do not time out.
  * Add src/va_test.c: synthetic VA-API decode correctness test for VP9.

 -- Eduardo García-Mádico Portabella <woodyst@gmail.com>  Wed, 28 May 2026 04:00:00 +0000

rockchip-vaapi (1.0.7-1) noble; urgency=high

  * Fix NS_ERROR_DOM_MEDIA_FATAL_ERR crash at quality transitions: BeginPicture
    no longer closes the surface's prime_fd. Firefox calls ExportSurfaceHandle
    from a compositor thread without SyncSurface while EndPicture polls MPP;
    prime_fd was -1 causing ERROR_INVALID_SURFACE. Now BeginPicture keeps the
    previous fd (placeholder or last decoded frame) valid; assign_mpp_frame
    replaces it atomically when the real decoded frame arrives.
  * assign_mpp_frame: update s->width/s->height from actual decoded frame
    dimensions so ExportSurfaceHandle reports the correct stride after a DASH
    quality switch (mismatch between surface width and pitch was also causing
    NS_ERROR_DOM_MEDIA_FATAL_ERR in earlier sessions).
  * do_h264_decode / do_generic_decode: add pre-drain loop before
    decode_put_packet to consume frames MPP already has queued from previous
    packets; reduce EndPicture poll window from 500ms to 100ms.
  * SyncSurface: extend drain timeout from 2s to 3s.

 -- Eduardo García-Mádico Portabella <woodyst@gmail.com>  Wed, 28 May 2026 01:00:00 +0000

rockchip-vaapi (1.0.6-1) noble; urgency=high

